text: Queen Caroline may refer to: * Caroline of Ansbach (1683–1737), queen of the Kingdom of Great Britain * Maria Carolina of Austria (1752–1814), queen of Naples * Caroline of Brunswick (1768–1821), queen of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland * Caroline Matilda of Great Britain (1751–1775), queen of Norway and Denmark * Queen Caroline Estate, a council housing development in Hammersmith & Fulham, London
title: Queen Caroline
